body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for reaching out to CarFix Solutions. My name is Jordan Collins. May I kindly ask for your name?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Christina. To assist you better, could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five six seven eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Christina. Additionally, may I ask for your home address for our records?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my address is two three four Main Street, Anytown, USA.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for providing your contact details. Now, could you describe the pricing issue you are facing to better assist you?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling sad because the pricing for the service I received was much higher than expected.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand how that can be frustrating, Christina. Thank you for sharing your concern. We will work to resolve this for you. Thank you for your time today!
